HEADWORD: Glycyrrhizin
<hw>Gly*cyr"rhi*zin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>glycyrrhizine</ets>. See <er>Glycyrrhiza</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A glucoside found in licorice root
(<prodby><gen>Glycyrrhiza</gen></prodby>), in monesia bark
(<prodby><gen>Chrysophyllum</gen></prodby>), in the root of the walnut,
etc., and extracted as a yellow, amorphous powder, of a bittersweet
taste.</def></p>

